		"description": "<p>You have learned to manipulate your own blood in ways that arguably make you more monstrous, but also make you much more dangerous to the monsters you fight. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Half your bloodblade levels count as ranger levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.g78ee57oirh51tek]{Adversarial Focus} feature.</li>\n<li>When you reduce a creature with a CR of at least half your character level to 0 hit points with a melee attack, you can use a bonus action to absorb its blood into yourself. If you do so, choose one of the following options:\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>You are sustained, as if you had just consumed a unit of Supply.</li>\n<li>You recover a level of fatigue.</li>\n<li>You regain 2 points of exertion.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Once you have used this benefit a number of times equal to half your proficiency bonus, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Your altered physiology grants you the ability to briefly focus your senses beyond the limits of ordinary mortals. As a bonus action, you can spend a hit die to do any of the following:\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>You gain truesight with a range of 30 feet until the beginning of your next turn.</li>\n<li>Your hearing sharpens to a superhuman degree. You have blindsight with a range of 120 feet until the beginning of your next turn.</li>\n<li>Your smell becomes as sharp as a bloodhound&rsquo;s. You have advantage on Perception and Investigation checks involving smell until the beginning of your next turn, and you can automatically detect poisoned food or drink by sniffing it.</li>\n<li>You can see distant objects with greater clarity. You have advantage on Perception checks based on sight to see things or distinguish details at long range, and you can use ranged weapons out to their maximum range without incurring disadvantage until the beginning of your next turn.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You can only have one of these enhancements active at a time.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>",
